shiny.omicron 0.0.0.9000
  • Reference

    Reference

    All functions

    basemap

    A base map of the world. Country names are renamed to match the data from covariants

    country_list

    A list of all countries available in the data.

    dates_list

    A list of all available dates in the global data

    heatmap_theme()

    Heatmap Theme this is the base theme to apply to all of the heatmaps

    map_dominant_variant()

    Map Dominan Variant map based on the most prevalent variant for a given week

    map_variant()

    Map Variant map based on a selected variant for a given week

    omicron_global_proportions

    A list of percentage of total covid cases are each individual variant combined across all countries

    omicron_proportions

    A list of percentage of total covid cases are each individual variant stratified by week and country

    plot_heatmap_by_country()

    Plot Heatmap by Country plots a heatmap by country and date for a specific variant

    plot_heatmap_by_lineage()

    Plot Heatmap By Lineage plots a heatmap of proportion of each variant globally to give a sense of dominant variant over time.

    plot_proportions()

    Plot Proportions

    prep_maps()

    Prepare Maps Merge dataframe with world geometries on country column

    theme_map()

    Theme Map Removes the axis from a plotly plot

    variant_list

    A list of all available variants
